      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Chris Whittington</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:152px;\"><a href=\"http://www.rebel.nl/authors.htm\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/e/e8/Chrisw.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"193\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Chrisw.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Chris Whittington <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Chris Whittington</b>,<br />\na British computer chess and games programmer, publisher and entrepreneur, author of several commercial computer chess programs including <a href=\"/Chess_System_Tal\" title=\"Chess System Tal\">Chess System Tal</a> published through his own company <a href=\"/Oxford_Softworks\" title=\"Oxford Softworks\">Oxford Softworks</a>. He is famous for his computer chess paradigms as an appeal for knowledge based programs <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. In May 2000, when Oxford Softworks was sold to a venture capitalist consortium, Chris retired from games programming. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Rybka_Controversy\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Rybka Controversy</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Photos\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Photos</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Chess_Engines\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Chess Engines</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#1997_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1997 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#2015_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2015 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#2020_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2020 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Rybka_Controversy_2\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Rybka Controversy</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Minority_Reports\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Minority Reports</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Rybka_Controversy\">Rybka Controversy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Rybka Controversy\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>Chris Whittington was and is critic of the arguments that <a href=\"/Rybka\" title=\"Rybka\">Rybka</a> is a derivate of <a href=\"/Fruit\" title=\"Fruit\">Fruit</a> since <a href=\"/Zach_Wegner\" title=\"Zach Wegner\">Zach Wegner</a> published his first conclusion on the Rybka/Fruit: evaluation in June 2010 <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>, and consequently critic of the <a href=\"/ICGA\" title=\"ICGA\">ICGA</a> <a href=\"/Rybka_Controversy#RybkaDecision\" title=\"Rybka Controversy\">decision</a> in 2011. During the <a href=\"/ICGA_Investigations\" title=\"ICGA Investigations\">Investigation process</a>, he was rejected to become member of the <a href=\"/ICGA_Investigations#Panel\" title=\"ICGA Investigations\">panel</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>.  \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Photos\">Photos</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Photos\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"http://www.thorstenczub.de/hiarcs.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Chrisandberthold2.jpg\" src=\"/images/f/f5/Chrisandberthold2.jpg\" width=\"497\" height=\"345\" style=\"vertical-align: text-bottom\" class=\"thumbborder\" /></a></div> \n<p>Chris Whittington and <a href=\"/index.php?title=Berthold_Seifriz&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Berthold Seifriz (page does not exist)\">Berthold Seifriz</a>, <a href=\"/WMCCC_1993\" title=\"WMCCC 1993\">WMCCC 1993</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Chess_Engines\">Chess Engines</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Chess Engines\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/SuperChess\" title=\"SuperChess\">SuperChess</a> (1982)</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Chess_Player_2150\" title=\"Chess Player 2150\">Chess Player 2150/2175</a> (1989)</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Chess_Simulator\" title=\"Chess Simulator\">Chess Simulator</a> (1990)</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Complete_Chess_System\" title=\"Complete Chess System\">Complete Chess System</a> (1993)</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Chess_System_Tal\" title=\"Chess System Tal\">Chess System Tal</a> (Complete Chess System 2) (1995)</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Chess_System_Tal\" title=\"Chess System Tal\">Chess System Tal II</a> (1999)</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/4th_Computer_Olympiad#PromotionBug\" title=\"4th Computer Olympiad\">Computer Olympiad 1992 - Promotion Bug</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/WMCCC_1995#TalXXXX\" title=\"WMCCC 1995\">WMCCC 1995 - System Tal vs XXXX</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1997_...\">1997 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 1997 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://groups.google.com/group/rec.games.chess.computer/browse_frm/thread/b08d2a90de4f0ca6\">CW and the ICCA</a> by <a href=\"/Tony_Marsland\" title=\"Tony Marsland\">Tony Marsland</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, February 26, 1997&#160;» <a href=\"/ICCA\" title=\"ICCA\">ICCA</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://groups.google.com/group/rec.games.chess.computer/browse_frm/thread/79a90bb9548486fe\">Formal Appeal to CCC Moderators</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, August 16, 1998</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2015_...\">2015 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: 2015 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.foro.meca-web.es/viewtopic.php?f=9&amp;t=72&amp;start=50#p9325\">Re: La Máquina Preservadora. Programas de Ajedrez</a> by duct, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Meca Foro</a>, May 20, 2016 (Spanish)</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=32398\">AlphaZero reinvents mobility and romanticism</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, December 08, 2017&#160;» <a href=\"/AlphaZero#ImmortalZugzwang\" title=\"AlphaZero\">Alpha Zero's \"Immortal Zugzwang Game\"</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/lczero/S-rhiPLnbHg/XY9-Z1LWCAAJ\">Who entered Leela into WCCC? Bad idea!!</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">LCZero Forum</a>, June  23, 2018&#160;» <a href=\"/Leela_Chess_Zero\" title=\"Leela Chess Zero\">Leela Chess Zero</a>, <a href=\"/WCCC_2018\" title=\"WCCC 2018\">WCCC 2018</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=69942\">categorical cross entropy for value</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 18, 2019</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=70328\">Analysis of policy nets</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 27, 2019&#160;» <a href=\"/Deep_Learning\" title=\"Deep Learning\">Deep Learning</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=70584\">Wouldn't it be nice if C++ GPU</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 25, 2019&#160;» <a href=\"/GPU\" title=\"GPU\">GPU</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=70611\">SL vs RL</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 28, 2019&#160;» <a href=\"/Monte-Carlo_Tree_Search\" title=\"Monte-Carlo Tree Search\">MCTS</a>, <a href=\"/Deep_Learning\" title=\"Deep Learning\">Deep Learning</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=71269\">Wouldn’t it be nice if there was a ChessNet50</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 13, 2019&#160;» <a href=\"/Neural_Networks\" title=\"Neural Networks\">Neural Networks</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2020_...\">2020 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: 2020 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=73129\">EPD destruction tests</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 19, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Engine_Testing\" title=\"Engine Testing\">Engine Testing</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=73208\">EPD destruction tests, part 2</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 27, 2020</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=73812\">Request for InDoubleCheck PERFTS EPDs</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 02, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Double_Check\" title=\"Double Check\">Double Check</a>, <a href=\"/Perft\" title=\"Perft\">Perft</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=75088\">SMP, first shot at implementation</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 12, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Lazy_SMP\" title=\"Lazy SMP\">Lazy SMP</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=75116\">Memory management and threads</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 15, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Memory\" title=\"Memory\">Memory</a>, <a href=\"/Thread\" title=\"Thread\">Thread</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Rybka_Controversy_2\">Rybka Controversy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Rybka Controversy\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-chess.org/viewtopic.php?f=3&amp;t=301#p2658\">Re: What do you folks make of this&#160;?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">OpenChess Forum</a>, June 27, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=23292\">setjmp() - another one</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 27, 2008</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-chess.org/viewtopic.php?f=3&amp;t=1032\">Without the Clean Room</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Chris Whittington</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Open Chess Forum</a>, January 26, 2011</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Minority_Reports\">Minority Reports</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Minority Reports\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=22370\">Minority Report Plagiarism - Quantifying Evaluation Features</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Trotsky</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, July 09, 2011</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=22486\">Minority Report 2 - Unravelling the technical report</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Trotsky</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, July 22, 2011</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=22502\">Minority Report 3, PST + other lookup tables are they legal?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Trotsky</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, July 25, 2011</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=22587\">Minority Report 4, How can something so trivial be copyright</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Trotsky</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, August 06, 2011</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=23046\">Minority Report 5, Not plagiarism unless feature is unique</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Trotsky</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, September 21, 2011</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.game-ai-forum.org/icga-tournaments/person.php?id=48\">Chris Whittington's ICGA Tournaments</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/ChrisWhittington\">ChrisWhittington · GitHub</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.rebel.nl/authors.htm\">Meet the Authors</a> by <a href=\"/Ed_Schroder\" title=\"Ed Schroder\">Ed Schröder</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.mobygames.com/developer/sheet/view/developerId,96374/\">Chris Whittington - Developer BIO</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MobyGames\">MobyGames</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseekpub.cgi?regexp=%5EChris+Whittington$&amp;loadpics=1\">Chris Whittington - World of Spectrum</a></li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseekid.cgi?id=0000116\">Airbase Invader - World of Spectrum</a></dd></dl>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chris_Whittington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.rebel.nl/authors.htm\">Meet the Authors</a> by <a href=\"/Ed_Schroder\" title=\"Ed Schroder\">Ed Schröder</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thorstenczub.de/complcss2.html\">Complete Chess System 2 - TAL</a> from <a href=\"/Thorsten_Czub\" title=\"Thorsten Czub\">Thorsten Czub's</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thorstenczub.de/scw.html\">Schachcomputerwelt</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">